


1. How would you recover your data after a machine with an in-memory database reboots or crashes. ?
2. Well, with just an in-memory database, there’s no way out. A machine is down — the data is lost. Forget about it.
3. Is it possible to combine the power of in-memory data storage and the durability of good old databases like MySQL or Postgres?.
4. Sure! Would it affect the performance? Surprisingly, it won’t!


5. Here come in-memory databases with persistence like Redis, Aerospike, Tarantool.